American Seafoods is a frozen seafood processing facility that utilizes anhydrous ammonia as a refrigerant. Anhydrous Ammonia is considered hazardous by the Environmental Protection Agency and the smaame properties that make ammonia a valuable refrigerant also makes it necessary to observe certain safety precautions. To prevent exposure to our workers, surrounding communtiy and the environment, it is our policy to implement the requirements of the Risk Management Program by: Managing and operating this facility in full compliance with all applicable federal and state regulations that we are gover. Forwarding copies of our Emergency response plan to the Local Fire Department and Local Emergency Response Comission. Informing the community of the potentail hazards and minimize the risk of an accidental release. Our plant personnel have been trained on the equipment operating procedures and various safety devices, which are incorporated in our facility to prevent the possibilty of an accidental release. Key employees have been trained to isolate areas within the refrigeration system, which may become hazardous. These employees have attended the 24 hour emergency response training course in ammonia refrigeration and attend the annual eight (8) hour refresher course. Safety depends on our proper handling of Anhydrous Ammonia in this facility and American Seafoods will ensure that the safety of its employees comes first. The following engineering controls are in place at American Seafoods International LLC. These controls are designed to reduce the possibilities of an accidental release. Electronic Ammonia Detection system is installed in the refrigeration room and other areas within the system.
